items.name: epiCPhotoGasm
items.description:
Welcome to epiCPhotoGasm

This Model is highly tuned for Photorealism with the tiniest amount of exessive prompting needed to shine.
All Showcase images are generated without Negatives (V1) to show what is possible on the bare prompt.

Whats special?

The model has highly knowledge of what a photo is, so if u promt u can avoid using photo. If the prompt tends to be fantasy like the model will turn away from photo and u have to tweak by prompting and/or negatives.

The model can do various ethnicities well, so try them out.

Age is also well trained and known by the model, so try them out too.

How to use

  • use simple prompts without "fake" enhancers like "masterpiece, photorealistic, 4k, 8k, super realistic, realism" etc.

  • don't use a ton of negative embeddings, focus on few tokens or single embeddings

  • you can still use atmospheric enhances like "cinematic, dark, moody light" etc.

  • start sampling at 20 Steps

  • no extra noise-offset needed

Additional Ressources

Style Negatives: colorful Photo | soft Photo

Useful Extensions

!After Detailer | ControlNet | Agent Scheduler | Ultimate SD Upscale

⭐ Feel free to leave Reviews and Samples - and always have fun creating ❤

Marathon Infinity Monsters
items.description:
A model to create images of the monsters that appear in Bungie's classic FPS, Marathon Infinity.

The images in this model are straight output using the NightvisionXL checkpoint. No upscaling or enhancing was done. You can likely get better results by upscaling or doing an img2img pass.

If you find yourself getting low quality backgrounds that look like they're from Marathon, you can try putting 'video game background' in the negative prompt. You also may want to lower the weight of the lora a bit.

Along with the monster trigger words, you can also control which direction they're facing by using the words:
facing forward
facing at a 45 degree angle
facing sideways
facing away

items.name: Creative censorship | ComfyUI workflow
items.description:
This workflow automates the process of putting stickers on picture.

How it works

Generate stickers → Remove background → Put it in the center of each mask region

Installation and dependencies

  1. Install WAS Node Suite custom nodes, or just Rembg custom node;

  2. Install Masquerade custom nodes;

  3. Download and open this workflow.

Extra installation (optional, for automatic masking)

  1. Install Impact Pack custom nodes;

  2. Download NudeNet model and place it into "ComfyUI/models/onnx".

Note

If you draw masks manually, in Mask Editor, you only need to make small blots. Only centers matter.

Known issues

Automatic masking with NudeNet is flawed in many ways:

  • navels are always detected as assholes

  • center of breast region is not on a nipple

  • too close neighboring masks will conjoin together

  • NudeNet is better for anime, and constantly struggles with realistic nudes

  • some needed functionality is currently undoable with Impact pack (as for 22 Aug 2023). Check for updates.

It is reasonable to go for manual masking only, just deleting the whole node group for automated masking.

Check out my other workflows

items.name: Lady Furina / Focalors <Genshin Impact> | 芙宁娜/芙卡洛斯 <原神>
items.description:
Lady Furina from Genshin Impact, dress her up however you like!

Recommended parameters

Sampler: DPM++ 2S a Karras;

Steps: 35-45;

LoRA weight: 0.85-0.9

Base model for training: MeinaMix V11

Prompting guide

lady_furina will give you Furina herself. If you use highres fix, try not to make denoise strength higher than 0.35, or the heterochromia detail might get lost. A potential fix is to use ADetailer, write (heterochromia, dark blue and light blue eyes) in positive prompt, adjust the weight as needed.

focalors_outfit will give Furina her default in-game look. I recommend using it in tandem with lady_furina, with 1.5 weight, such as 1girl, lady_furina, (focalors_outfit:1.5), but 1girl, focalors_outfit would also work. I find that with lady_furina the model is more expressive when it comes to Furina herself, but it's not conclusive.

As to other propmt tags, expression and action should get the most weight, clothing style behind that, and then background/location, perhaps 1.6, 1.3, 1.2 respectively. This is because the training images don't depict Furina with a lot of expressions, but backgrounds are rather flexible as I removed all of them before training.

You can use this LoRA on realistic style models, it will likely give you a Furina cosplayer :P

Training Method

Dataset: the dataset is separated into two concepts. lady_furina and focalors_outfit, all images come from in-game cutscene screenshots and fanart from Google, most of them generated by AI. I then remove the background and exaggerate her heterochromia. For images in focalors_outfit, I fix the color of her gloves, as most of them were generated by previous AI models and the color were most likely wrong. While testing tagging mothods, some good results from the previous iterations of this model get processed and put into the dataset.

Tagging: in addition to deepbooru auto tagging, lady_furina images get all biological feature tags removed, while keeping tags about her clothing. focalors_outfit images get all biological feature tags and clothing tags removed. Composition tags such as full body, camera from below, front view are added to mitigate potential stiffness in generated images.

Training: I tried the lion optimizer, turns out even at 1.5e-5 lr and 3e-6 text_lr it still learns too fast. Every epoch I set lady_furina (21 images) as 30 and focalors_outfit (11 images) as 60, but after 3 epochs the model got very stiff and stick only to what it was trained on. This model is the 2nd epoch result.

If anyone wants to share their two cents on how to improve the training procedure, please don't hesitate to comment, I am eager to learn better methods. Meanwhile for everyone else, enjoy playing dress-up with Furina :P

items.name: 【再世】next life-夏萍（卢少萍）
items.description:
这是群星再世第八十四期，以后会不定期出去世的群星Lora，以纪念他们。

夏萍生于1937年，于1955年她投考了电影公司成为演员，1970年她加入邵氏电影拍片13年，至1982年加入无线电视至2016年，横跨演艺圈60年，是圈中出名金牌绿叶的老戏骨，香港影视圈甘草演员，一生几乎没有主演过影视剧目，但在港片里无论在古装或者时装，角色均以母亲、祖母、姑婆、道姑及佣工为主，年轻时的拍摄的电影也主要是一家里的长女，情妇，美貌妇人等为主。

大家或许都觉得她的样子经常出现在影视作品里，却有时候又难以想起来，夏萍曾在周星驰《九品芝麻官》中饰演包龙星的老妈。电视作品包括《法证先锋》、《寻秦记》、《金装四大才子》、《烈火雄心》、《刑事侦缉档案》系列、《陀枪师姐》系列等等都有她的身影，一生有记录的参演影视剧集拍摄超过300多部。

2016年，77岁的夏萍荣获“万千星辉演艺大奖”，相当于终身成就奖，只有那些你能经常看到的金牌演员才能获得此殊荣。

2019年夏萍因病去世，享年81岁。

这届话事人，我选东莞仔，他为社团翻过栏杆，还有情有义。夏萍有一年拍戏和林家栋饰演母子，夏萍对当时迷茫的林家栋指引方向，解除困惑，后来收林家栋为契仔（干儿子），夏萍人生的最后十年就是林家栋照顾的。

ps：夏萍（old）的素材选自1953年——1970年之间的十余部不同老电影，但是那些电影黑线，噪点，曝光太多，所以出图的时候一定会受到影响，这个问题没有办法解决。这些素材里，95%都是黑白照片，如果跑图出了彩色图片，一定质量会很差很差。

ps2：夏萍（old）素材中的一部分，夏萍穿的是睡衣和内衣等比较暴露的衣服，彩色照片会出现一小部分比较暴露的图，请尊重逝者。

这个lora我从规划到收集素材用了二十四天。。。找那些老港片实在是太难了，想象不到的难，二十，三十年的还算不得真正意义上的老港片，这种六七十年的才真的难找。

Important: This is natural fine-tuning trained with LyCORIS (algo=full, preset=attn-mlp, trained_norm=True), please make sure you have the at least a1111 webui version 1.6.0 to use it

All the intermediate checkpoints are available at: https://huggingface.co/alea31415/world-witches-series

The current model is trained on anime + fan art for luminous witches and fan art only for the remaining, so I expect it to perform better for luminous witches

Characters included (correspondance with booru tags are provided at the end)

Luminous Witches: Aila, Ginny, Ellie, Gracie, Joanna, Milasha, Manaia, Shibuya Inori, Sylvie, Maria, Nishisugi Tomomi

Brave Witches: Nikka, Georgette, Sasha, Kanno Naoe, Shimohara Sadako, Karibuchi Hikari, Karibuchi Takami, Waltrud Krupinski, Edytha Rossmann, Gundula Rall, Misumi Miya

Strike Witches: Miyafuji Yoshika, Sanya, Eila, Minna, Perrine, Lynette, Erica, Charlotte, Gertrud, Lucchini, Sakamoto Mio, Yamakawa Michiko, Ursula Hartmann, Hattori Shizuka

Others: Kuroda Kunika, Hanna-justina Marseille, Heidimarie, Hanna Wind, Takei Junko, Anabuki Tomoko, Aurora e Juutilainen, Wilma Bishop, Raisa Pottgen, Helma Lennartz, Heinrike, Rosalie, Hanna Rudel, Fernandia Malvezzi, Marian e Carl, Hannelore Kummel

During training, I use the tags aniscreen and fanart for anime screenshots and fan arts respectively, but I do not recommend using them for image generation (unless you want particularly the anime screencap style)

Wallpaper is used on very few images, and cause severe overfitting, so you should not use it as is but may still be interesting for i2i or when used as [:wallpaper:0.5]

—

Caveats:

Only characters are learned. That means that neither outfits, familiars, nor different forms are tagged properly, so to trigger them you may need to play with the prompts. Also, when you find something to be present too often even if you do not put it in the prompt, you can try to put it in negative, such as hirschgeweih antennas for Ginny

items.name: Crowds
items.description:
(Still experimental and I'm getting mixed results)

Generate background crowds with just a depth map and an OpenPose file.

To make this work, you need to activate multi ControlNet in Settings -> ControlNet -> Multi ControlNet: Max models amount. I have this set to 4. Requires a restart.

Workflow

  • Drop the background OpenPose file into ControlNet Unit 0, Control Weight 0.5. Rest stays at default.

  • Drop the depth map into ControlNet Unit 1, Control Weight 0.35 (may need to be tweaked some; sometimes 0.3 works better). Rest stays at default.

  • Drop your foreground character's openpose file into ControlNet Unit 2, everything, including Control Weight, stays at default. This can be any pose of your choice. Ideally the aspect ratio matches the one of the 2 background files (they're all 3x2 or 2x3).

  • Obviously you need to set pre-processor to "none" for all of the 3 ControlNet units.

  • Useful key words for the prompt: "crowd, multiple_others" ("multiple_boys", "multiple_girls" if it applies). If you're generating a stadium or arena, you can add "spectators, arena, stadium". Or theater, courtroom, concert, etc. Generating scenes with crowded streets has also worked.

  • This looks like it might work best with depth of field (?).

  • Prompting at higher resolutions might generate more background character than going 768x512 or 512x768 (?). Still unsure about this. Many generations were just fine at low resolutions.

items.name: Female Celebrity Wildcard - Over 1,400 Known Celebrities - by Xenos
items.description:
This is a curated wildcard list of over 1,000 (1,095 at first release, to be exact) 1400 (Sept. 13, 2023) female celebrities from all different walks of life - from actresses to athletes to reality stars to porn stars and more. They have all been tested and generated on one of my three primary models: XenoEngine ArtStyle, XenoGASM, Kitsch-In-Sync, and/or XenoREALITY (see recommended list for links). They should work on MOST other models, too - but there are no guarantees.

A few Notes:

  • I did not include anyone who is currently or who ends up being generated looking like a child.

  • I did include some that may not hold up to extensive posing and scene detail. In other words - if you put the person's name into a prompt by itself, it definitely bears more than a passing resemblance to the person - but in some cases, the dataset is so small that if you start to add styles or change up clothing, other features and appearance details may bleed in.

  • Some of these end up looking like caricatures more than "photo real" versions of themselves. I'm not sure exactly what factor plays into this - something in the training data set, I would assume.

  • Some of these require a bit of work to make look good because of the training images. This is especially true for some of the older actresses. For example, Farrah Fawcett's (default) hair and general appearance can be a bit blurry since she was obviously trained on older scanned (and probably faded) images rather than modern digital photos.

  • Because of the above, be careful with your negative prompts. For example, if you are trying to make Farrah and put a lot of "low quality" and "blurry" type things in the negative prompt, you could very well block the model from having access to any photos of her, thus making it so the output will no longer look like Farrah. To solve this, start with no negatives and try to add positives which affect the hair details, contrast issues, and so on. THEN maybe sneak in one or two necessary negatives for the last few things you want to clean up.

Like it? Buy me a beer.
Want Tips, Tricks, Pix of Things We Can't Show on Civitai?
Join the XenoEngine Discord to discuss tips and tricks, complimentary Lora's and Embeds, and to post (and see) images not allowed here on Civitai.

items.name: Urban Graffiti
items.description:
My first SDXL lora. Decided to try things out with some urban graffiti. Throw graffiti on stuff! SDXL models should be able to produce similar results depending on your subject and prompt, but this definitely makes it a lot easier as it wants to cover surfaces in random graffiti tags and art. I've kept the lora small and lightweight, but it still seems to function quite well to add a touch of urban graffiti to everything.

You can play around with CFG and weights as you like but it should work fine at standard values.
